title: Guji - Danse Mormora Farm
excerpt:
Prominent peach iced tea balanced with black tea tannins. Roasted rice on the finish.

Varietal: Bourbon
Process: Natural
Region: Oromia, Ethiopia

title: POUR MORE Tee
excerpt: We went to our mates up the road at Plastisol Beach to bring you some Little Drum Coffee long sleeve tees. This unisex AS Colour top features a custom POUR MORE design on the back, and small Little Drum logo on the front left chest. For all you pour over aficionados, or anyone wanting to look fresh and represent local business, we got you.

title: AeroPress
excerpt:
Loved by coffee geeks and no nonsense people the world over. This is one piece of equipment that showcases How the variables of brewing coffee affect the cup.

Simple to use and easy to experiment with. Just play around with the coffee grind size, the amount of coffee used, the water temp & adjust the brew time.

These units have created a true cult following.

Pack comes with filters, funnel and stirrer.

title: Left Field Series - GESHA Roasted to Order
excerpt:
JAIRO ARCILLA GESHA EF1
REGION: Circasia, Quindio
VARIETAL: Gesha
PROCESS: Extended Fermentation
TASTING NOTES: Aroma of blueberry pie, bold stewed strawberry with berry tea and slight lemongrass.

Side note: originating from Ethiopia, gesha coffee is prized for it’s outstanding flavour profile and sought after worldwide. The extended ferment process for these beans includes an 84hr anaerobic fermentation then the cherries are dried on raised beds.

**This coffee is roasted to order, we recommend waiting 5 days for degassing before brewing to allow the beans to really come in their own. BUT if you’re desperate, or impatient, or you just want to have a play, feel free – you still won’t be disappointed**

title: Cascara Tea
excerpt:
Bright apple juice with a floral background, lingering subtle dried apricot. Region: Columbia. Varietal: Caturra + Castillo. Process method: washed.

Cascara tea is made from the dried skins of coffee cherries (the fruit that grows around the beans). To brew use 40g per 1L of water, brew at 90 degrees celsius and steep for 4min, or longer if desired. Yield 2.5L tea from a 100g bag.
